<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00056</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REQUIRING ALL GRADUATING ELEMENTARY, HIGH SCHOOL AND COLLEGE STUDENTS TO PLANT AT LEAST TEN (10) TREES EACH AS A PREREQUISITE FOR GRADUATION AND FOR OTHER RELATED PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : "Graduation Legacy For The Environment Act Of 2019"

Seeks to impose a positive duty upon all graduating elementary, high school and college students to plant at least ten (10) trees as a prerequisite for graduation.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>CABOCHAN, MANUEL III. D.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB06931</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON REFORESTATION ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>